{{italic title}}
'''''Shōichi-kokushi Hōgo''''' (聖一国師法語) is Japanese Buddhist work.

== Authorship and date ==
''Shōichi-kokushi Hōgo'', a Japanese Buddhist work in one volume,{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} was composed in the late [[Kamakura period]]{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} by the monk [[Enni]].{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}}

== Title ==
Alternative titles for the work include ''Shōichi-kokushi Kana Hōgo'' (聖一国師仮名法語),{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} ''Tōfukuji Kaisan Shōichi-kokushi Hōgo'' (東福寺開山聖一国師法語),{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} ''Shōichi-kokushi Zazen-ron'' (聖一国師坐禅論),{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} and ''Zazen-ron'' (坐禅論).{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}}

== Contents ==
The work is of ''[[kana hōgo]]'' (仮名法語) genre,{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} a ''[[hōgo]]''<!-- Probably merits an article, per https://kotobank.jp/word/%E6%B3%95%E8%AA%9E-131941 --> written in colloquial Japanese, and was written by Enni to introduce [[Kujō Michiie]] to ''[[zazen]]'' (sitting meditation).{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} It consists of a general introduction and 24 sections expounding on Enni's answers to questions Michiie posed him regarding various aspects of ''zazen''.{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} An appendix dubbed "Kojin Hōgo" (古人法語) elaborates on points to be weary of in the practice of ''zazen''.{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}}

== Textual tradition and modern editions ==
Surviving manuscript copies of the work include the ''{{illm|Hōsa Bunko|ja|蓬左文庫}}-bon'',{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} the ''[[Kyoto University|Kyōto Daigaku]]-bon''{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} and the ''[[Ryukoku University|Ryūkoku Daigaku]]-bon''.{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} Printed editions were produced in 1646 ([[Shōhō|Shōhō 3]]),{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} 1648 ([[Keian|Keian 1]]){{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} and 1829 ([[Bunsei|Bunsei 12]]).{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}}

It was included in the first volume of the ''Kōtei Senchū Zenmon Hōgo Zenshū'' (校訂箋註禅門法語全集){{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}} and the second volume of the ''Zenmon Hōgo Shū'' (禅門法語集).{{sfnm|1a1=Imaeda|1y=1983|1p=327}}

